# Tailwind CSS v4 baseline — see docs/planning/tailwind-v4-migration.md.
#
# Tailwind v4 features (`@property`, `color-mix()`, container queries, native
# nesting, modern color tokens) require these minimums; older browsers degrade
# silently to broken layouts. We pin them here so any tooling that reads
# browserslist (caniuse-lite, eslint-plugin-compat, future PostCSS plugins)
# stays aligned with the engine's own support matrix.
#
# Vite/esbuild target is configured separately in `vite.config.js`
# (`build.target` defaults to native ES modules); changing this file does not
# alter the JS bundle target — it documents the *CSS* support contract for
# Tailwind utilities and any consumer of the published web app.
Safari >= 16.4
iOS >= 16.4
Chrome >= 111
ChromeAndroid >= 111
Firefox >= 128
FirefoxAndroid >= 128
Edge >= 111
Samsung >= 23
not dead
